value.value: Colorectal mutant cancer protein (829 aa, ~93 kDa) is encoded by the human MCC gene. This protein may be involved in modulation of the cell cycle.

E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase Mdm2 (491 aa, ~55 kDa) is encoded by the human MDM2 gene. This protein is involved in the mediation of the ubiquitination and degradation of protein substrates, and the inhibition of apoptosis induction that is mediated by cellular tumor antigen p53.
This gene plays a role in the degradation of oxidatively-damaged proteins in living cells.
Proteins that give shape to the nucleus and provide support for the chromosomes.

label.value: Probable Protein E4, Human Papillomavirus Type 6

value.value: Probable protein E4 is encoded by the human papillomavirus type 6 E4 gene. This protein is an early phase product and its function is unknown.
